  <h2 id="verdict">Our Verdict</h2>
  <p>
    Both AXA Global and Allianz Care are excellent choices for expats who want EU-regulated international health insurance. They're both backed by massive, financially stable insurance groups with decades of experience. You can't go seriously wrong with either provider.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Allianz Care</strong> offers better value for most expats. Their 15-25% lower pricing, modular flexibility, and aggressive high-deductible options make comprehensive coverage more accessible. The larger provider network and included telemedicine are additional advantages. For pure value, Allianz typically wins.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>AXA Global</strong> makes sense in specific situations. If you're moving to France or French-speaking countries, need coverage for a French visa application, or want the simplicity of bundled benefits without managing add-ons, AXA's premium over Allianz may be worth it. The Exclusive tier's unlimited coverage is also unique if you want maximum protection with no caps.
  </p>
  <p>
    Our recommendation for most expats: <strong>Allianz Care</strong> offers better overall value. Their lower premiums, modular approach, and competitive deductible options make them the smarter choice for budget-conscious expats who want comprehensive European-quality coverage.
  </p>
  <p>
    The exception: If you specifically need French connections (visa applications, French hospital relationships, French administrative familiarity), <strong>AXA Global</strong> is worth the premium.
  </p>
  <p>
    Get quotes from both providers for your specific situation. The actual price difference for your profile will help make the decision clear.
  </p>

