  <h2 id="faqs">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <h3>Is AXA Global or Allianz Care better?</h3>
  <p>
    Neither is universally better—it depends on your priorities. Allianz offers lower premiums and more flexibility through their modular approach. AXA offers bundled simplicity and has advantages for French visa applications. For pure value, Allianz typically wins. For specific French connections, AXA may be worth the premium.
  </p>

  <h3>Why is Allianz Care cheaper than AXA Global?</h3>
  <p>
    Allianz's modular approach means you only pay for coverage you choose. They also offer higher deductible options (up to €10,000) that can reduce premiums by up to 60%. AXA bundles more benefits into each tier, which costs more even if you don't need every included benefit.
  </p>

  <h3>Which provider has better coverage for Europe?</h3>
  <p>
    Both cover Europe excellently—they're both EU-headquartered companies with strong European networks. AXA has an edge in France and francophone countries. Allianz has advantages in German-speaking markets (though not available to German residents). For other European countries, either works well.
  </p>

  <h3>Are both providers accepted for EU visa applications?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes, both are EU-regulated and generally accepted for Schengen visa and long-stay visa applications. AXA has a specific advantage for French visa applications due to their French regulatory status and familiarity with French administrative requirements.
  </p>

  <h3>Which provider has better customer service?</h3>
  <p>
    Both receive mixed reviews—generally positive for routine interactions, with complaints about complex claims. Neither stands out as dramatically better. Both offer 24/7 multilingual support and professional service cultures.
  </p>

  <h3>Can I switch between these providers?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes, you can switch at any renewal period. However, switching triggers new underwriting, and any conditions that developed while on your previous policy could be treated as pre-existing by your new insurer. Consider this carefully before switching, especially if you've developed health issues.
  </p>

